  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-03-12",
    "date": "2020-04-03T15:45:18Z",
    "text": "This bill directs the Department of Transportation to issue regulations that require operators of cruise vessels or cruise lines to reimburse individuals for the ticket price of a cruise purchased on or before February 1, 2020, in the event of a cancellation due to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019).\n\nThe bill applies for the duration of any emergency declared with respect to COVID-19."
